Package com.olap3.cubeexplorer.data

Class CellSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.olap3.cubeexplorer.data.CellSet
  • public class CellSet
extends java.lang.Object

    This class act like a wrapper for the CellSet interface. The main purpose is to store the cell set values into an Double[][] for a simpler accessing, and provide utility methods

    "But why just not extends/implement CellSet ?" you may ask.

    When executing an MDX query, a CellSet implementation is retrieved. The implementation depends of which driver was used for the connection. Mondrian for example return an MondrianOlap4jCellSet which is a private class ! That means we can't extends it (curse you Mondrian !).

    This class is also named CellSet, that may be stupid. Feel free to change it if you find a better name. Maybe "Dashboard", or something like "CubeBoard" ? ... "DashCube" ?
